Twin Bombings Kill 73 People in Pakistan’s Charsadda, Injuring 68 Others

-- B y   K h u r r u m   A n i s
-- 
2011-05-13T03:15:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/twin-bombings-kill-73-people-in-pakistan-s-charsadda-injuring-68-others.html
Twin bombings in  Pakistan ’s
northwestern city of Charsadda left 73 people dead and 68 were
injured, Zia Ullah, a police officer, said by telephone.  One bomb was planted in a motorcycle, Jahanzeb Khan, a
police inspector told reporters in Charsadda. The bombs exploded
as cadets from the Frontier Constabulary, a paramilitary force,
were going home after their graduation ceremony, GEO television
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khurrum Anis in Karachi at 
